{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d63776d0-e81c-4057-a0aa-92f4166be612","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob (`**\\*.*`)\n**File:** `EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 9\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is one of the most expensive operations possible — it scales with the number of files on disk and re-runs on every evaluation (design-time builds, IntelliSense, etc.). Narrow the glob to specific extensions or directories.\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function during evaluation\n**File:** `EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 13\n```xml\n<BuildNotes …>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` is a **property function that performs disk I/O at evaluation time**. Property functions run synchronously during the evaluation pass, blocking the entire process. This should be moved to a target that runs at build time instead.\n\n### 3. Chained import depth (3 levels)\n**Files:** `level1.props` → `level2.props` → `level3.props`\n\nThe import chain is 3 levels deep. Each `<Import>` adds evaluation overhead (file existence checks, XML parsing, property/item merging). While 3 levels is moderate, it's worth noting because:\n- Each level currently contributes only a single property — they could be **flattened** into one file.\n- Deep import chains become much worse when combined with the other issues above, as evaluation cost is multiplicative.\n\n---\n\n### Summary (priority order)\n\n| Issue | Impact | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` glob | 🔴 High | Scope to specific extensions/dirs |\n| `File::ReadAllText` at eval | 🟠 Medium | Move to a build target |\n| 3-level import chain | 🟡 Low | Flatten into one `.props` file |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f6f175ec-e5cf-4d0f-a517-353b6579f98f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":551},"id":"dd2b0fd0-40df-4211-b6b5-1da0b1824616","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:07:13.860Z","parentId":"c9384255-bdc4-4959-9b31-a0f84537a400"}
